&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Radar Reinvented.&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;Echodyne offers the world’s first compact solid-state true beam-steering radar for a wide range of industries and applications. Our high-performance radars work in all weather and are designed for autonomous vehicles, uncrewed aircraft &amp;amp; drones, and security of borders, critical infrastructure, and smart cities. The company combines the patented technology of metamaterials with powerful software to create a radar sensor with unprecedented performance at commercial price points. Echodyne offers its radars to companies working in Automotive, Transportation, Critical Infrastructure Protection, Border Security, Smart Cities, Uncrewed Aircraft Systems (UAS), and Airspace Management including Urban Air Mobility (UTM).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 92, 185);&quot; data-darkreader-inline-color=&quot;&quot;&gt;Echodyne is seeking Antenna Production Engineers to join our fast-growing team and even faster-growing production facilities.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Echodyne, we don’t just believe radar makes the world safer and more secure; we know it. Echodyne employees see the proof of it every day, and in this role, your work will directly and observably support our mission of “Safety and Security in an Age of Autonomy.&quot;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 92, 185);&quot; data-darkreader-inline-color=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;RESPONSIBILITIES&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Antenna Production Engineering team will own the maintenance and evolution of all antenna and radar test &amp;amp; measurement instruments. &amp;nbsp;Members of this team will be responsible for ensuring that antenna ATP instruments maintain operational uptime that supports production targets, for identifying and leading upgrades, and will work with the manufacturing team as SMEs supporting expansions of Echodyne’s production facilities. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 92, 185);&quot; data-darkreader-inline-color=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;REQUIRED SKILLS / EXPERIENCE&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;BS Degree or higher in Engineering or Physics&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2 or more years of experience in antennas or antenna-measurement.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understanding of the fundamentals of antennas and antenna measurement.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hands-on experience measuring antennas or radiating RF devices at microwave and/or millimeter-wave frequencies. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience performing data analysis for measurement/experiments, related to antenna measurement, including pattern analysis, side-lobes, and near/far field transformations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Some experience writing code for analysis, applications, or projects.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: #005cb9;&quot; data-darkreader-inline-color=&quot;&quot;&gt;DESIRED SKILLS / EXPERIENCE&amp;nbsp; &lt;br&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;(Looking for one or more as a complement to the core skills)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hands-on experience with complex mixed-signal (RF, analog, &amp;amp; digital) instruments or experimental apparatus.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in any mechanical engineering CAD programs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Aptitude for building things, and hands-on proactive approach to what needs to get done.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 92, 185);&quot; data-darkreader-inline-color=&quot;&quot;&gt;CULTURAL NORTH STAR&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&g

